               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 3r-22va)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse “The Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 22va-55va)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     55va-153vb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 55va-69va)
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 69va-73vb)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our
                     Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 73vb-83vb)
 III-4) Anaphora of St
                     John, son of Thunder (fols. 83vb-92va)
 III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox
                     Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 92va-100va)
 III-6) Anaphora of St Athanasius of
                     Alexandria (fols. 100va-110va)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea
                     (fols. 110va-118ra)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St
                     Gregory”) (fols. 118ra-123vb)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus
                     (fols. 123vb-130ra)
 III-10) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols.
                     130ra-145rb)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols.
                     145rb-151ra)
 III-12) Second Anaphora of St Gregory (“Christmas-liturgy of
                     St Gregory”) (fols. 151ra-153vb)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
