                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1"> <locus target="#154r">f. 154r</locus>
                           <desc>: Rhymed donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#154r">154r</locus>: ለዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘቄስ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ሐሬነት፨
                              ዘተሣየጣ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ከመ፡ ትኵኖ፡ መድኃኒተ፡ ነፍስ፡ ወሥጋ። ምስለ፡ አቡሁ፡ {ገብረ፡} ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡
                              ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ {ገብርኤል፡} እለ፡ ወለድዋ፡ በጸጋ። ወያቁሞሙ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በደረ፡[sic] ጽዮን፡
                              እንግልጋ። ወምግባራቲሆሙ፡ ይምልአ፡ መዳልወ፡ ሕይወት፡ እንበለ፡ ንትጋ። ወኢያርእዮሙ፡ ለባሕረ፡ ሲኦል፡ ዱጋ።
                              ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም። አሜን። ዘወሀባ፡ ለደብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ገበዘይት። ኦአበውየ፡ ወአኃውየ። አማኅፀንኩክሙ፡
                              {በ}እግዚአብሔር፡ ልዑል፡ ወበወላዲቱ፡ ድንግል፡ ኢትርስኡኒ፡ በጊዜ፡ ጸሎት፡ ወቍርባን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note contains rhymed supplication for the donor and his
                              parents. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Notes in the upper margin: <locus target="#17r">17r</locus>, 37r, 128r.
 - Supplication to the Virgin Mary, in
                           poetic form, in the upper margin: <locus target="#22v">22v</locus>, 23r,
                           23v, 24r, 24v.
 - Beginning of P<locus target="#22">22</locus>,
                           crudely written in ink of different colours, possibly as writing
                           exercises: <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>, 32va-vb.
 - Verses from
                           various Psalms, crudely written in different secondary hands, in ink of
                           different colours: <locus target="#154va">154va-</locus>vb.
 - Crude
                           notes: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 1v, 2v, 153v, 154r, 155r,
                           155v.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Marginal note refer to the liturgical use of the
                              text. The respective Anaphora is indicated by the name of the feast
                              written in a frame: ዘሆሣዕና, <locus target="#118r">fol. 118r</locus>. -
                              Textile strip attached to the bottom of the leaf: <locus target="#127r">fol. 127r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
